50|$|A {{roll-out}} shelf, {{also known}} as a <b>glide-out</b> <b>shelf,</b> pull-out shelf or slide-out shelf is a shelf that can be moved forward on slides in order to more easily reach the contents stored {{in the back of a}} cupboard or cabinet. The slide mechanism can also be found in modern chests of drawers. Cabinet makers have been installing roll-out shelves for over 50 years.|$|E

